Claim: "Some people are seated on a bench outside."
Implication: "People are sitting on a bench in front of buildings."
Referring expressions: Some people, bench, outside.  People, bench, buildings
Formula: (exists c (exists a (exists b (IsSeatedOn(b,a) and IsOutside(c)))) & (forall f (forall h (forall g ( IsSeatedOn(f,g) ->  IsSittingOn(h,g))))) & (forall i (forall j (forall k ( IsSittingOn(i,j) ->  IsSeatedOn(k,j)))))) -> (exists e (exists a (exists d (IsSittingOn(d,a) and IsInFrontOf(e)))))
